				 Sinking coffin
																								Heavy rain lashing Nellore district of Andhra Pradesh since Sunday claimed 11 lives, including four minibus passengers.																								The four, part of a 25-member marriage party, had climbed the roof of the bus (in pictures), but could not save themselves. The others swam to safety.																								The state government has requisitioned two helicopters from Bangalore, but the air force choppers have not been able to land.																								Nellore, Prakasam, Kadapah and Chittoor districts have witnessed heavy rain over the past four days. Nellore received 22cm rainfall during the last 24 hours, officials said.																								Railway tracks are flooded at various places on the Ongole and Gudur sections of the Vijayawada division, railway sources said.																								Twenty passenger trains and 19 express trains have been cancelled. Eleven long- distance trains have been diverted. 																								About 40,000km of roads have been damaged. (PTI)
